==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cold wave
<hw>Cold" wave"</hw>. <fld>(Meteor.)</fld> <def>In the terminology of
the United States Weather Bureau, an unusual fall in temperature, to or
below the freezing point, exceeding 16⟦deg⟧ in twenty-four hours or
20⟦deg⟧ in thirty-six hours, independent of the diurnal range.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cole</ent>⟦br⟧
